snippet.textDisplay: Tbh, my first job almost broke me. I had no idea what I was doing, my boss was strict, and my coworkers barely talked to me. I went home exhausted every night. But I kept learning, kept showing up. Months later, the same people who ignored me started asking for my help. Hard work really does change things.

snippet.textDisplay: Depressed by Sasha Di Bartolomeo (accurately) @ 39:40 not @ 42:58 (the song queue is incorrect is selecting this one it will take you past most of the song).  The song starts again later in this video so this time stamp if for the first time.  Listening to this "track" reminds me of long hallways working alone nights, everything in the building is spartan like, just my thoughts and I and memories of a repressive past.  I am silently questioning what this life existence even is supposed to be, missing out on things in life that make it exciting and wondering if I can even create the experiences that make me feel what it feels like to be humanized of emotion after turning off the emotions for so many years.  I'll be at work listening to this in a state of an emotionless mental state and only knowledge is my assistant.  Work 12 to 13 hours on end day to day, from morning to night, no point wasting energy on pointless side quests, I see people and then they are not there, just me and the ghosts of those that once lived to accompany me through the night of the schools old and new until the lights go off and I come back to live to work another day.  What is the purpose of life, is this it?  Working to live a dream that seems to pull farther away by the year, another [birth] day, another year, just work, repeating the same motions losing a part of me in short disconnect from everyone working around Me, discontent, there has to be more  ...until then this is "it" repeating like an android.. is this "it"... this track is how I feel...
